1944;;Medal for the General;;British;;Maurice Elvey;;Godfrey Tearle, Jeanne De Casalis;;comedy;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medal_for_the_General;;The title character is Victor Church, a World War I veteran who becomes despondent when his advancing age prevents him from playing an active role in the battles of World War II. Feeling unwanted and useless, he retreats to his country estate and plans his suicide. He finds a new purpose in life when he opens his home to six rambunctious Cockney children evacuated from the London slums and tries to keep the mischievous group under control.